value.solution:
Surely it will work just fine.

Both nested functions are created within the same outer Lexical Environment, so they share access to the same `count` variable:

```js run
function Counter() {
  let count = 0;

  this.up = function() {
    return ++count;
  };

  this.down = function() {
    return --count;
